messages.content:
I have  c# wpf project with this code:

// MyProject/Utils/Constants/ToolTips.cs
namespace MyProject.Constants
{
    public static class ToolTips
    {
        public const string ToolTip1 = "ToolTip1";
        // Add more tooltip constants here if needed
    }
}

// MyProject/Views/Window.xaml
xmlns:c="clr-namespace:MyProject.Constants"

ToolTip="{x:Static c:ToolTips.ToolTip1}" //  error!

But it gives me error when accessing ToolTip1, how can I do that correctly

This error occurs because the XAML designer is looking for a code-behind file for your XAML view, but you have separated your XAML and code-behind files into separate folders. 

To fix this, you can create a code-behind file for your XAML view. Here's how:

1. Open your XAML view in Visual Studio.
2. Right-click on the XAML file in the Solution Explorer and select "View Code".
3. This will create a new code file with the same name as your XAML file (but with a ".xaml.cs" extension) in the same folder as your XAML file.
4. To move the code-behind file to your ViewModels folder, open the code file and replace the namespace declaration at the top of the file with the namespace for your ViewModels folder.
5. You will also need to update the class definition to inherit from the appropriate base class. In WPF, this is typically `System.Windows.Controls` or a related class. For example, if your XAML view is a `Window`, your class definition would look like this:

```csharp
namespace MyProject.ViewModels
{
    public partial class MyView : Window
    {
        public MyView()
        {
            InitializeComponent();
        }

        // Add event handlers here
    }
}
```

6. Once you have created the code-behind file and updated the namespace and class definition, you should be able to generate event handlers for your XAML controls without encountering the error you mentioned.
